        <updateDate>2025-05-23T13:57:57Z</updateDate>
        <cdata>
          <text>&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WOlf and Livestock Fairness Act of 2025 or the WOLF Act&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;strong&gt;of 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This bill directs the Department of Agriculture (USDA) to provide emergency relief to producers of livestock with herds adversely affected by Mexican gray wolves.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Specifically, the bill directs the Emergency Assistance for Livestock, Honey Bees, and Farm-Raised Fish Program (ELAP)&amp;nbsp;to provide emergency relief to producers of livestock with herds adversely affected by Mexican gray wolves. USDA must develop a formula to determine the amount of emergency relief to provide to a producer of livestock. Among other factors, the formula must take into consideration the herd size of the producer and the&amp;nbsp;average annual&amp;nbsp;increase in management costs for producers in the state due to Mexican gray wolves.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Additionally, the bill modifies USDA's Livestock Indemnity Program. In the case of attacks on livestock by Mexican gray wolves, the bill increases the&amp;nbsp;payment rate from 75% to 100% of the market value of the affected livestock.&lt;/p&gt;</text>
        </cdata>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
